The paper deals with learning user preferences, which is a core issue in AI research, and specifically focuses on learning CP-nets. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses learning-theoretic information complexity parameters, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper deals with combinatorial structures of CP-nets, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses algorithms for learning CP-nets, which falls under the scope of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the optimality of the algorithms, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
